<p class="p40" style="margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; text-indent: 0in; line-height: normal;" align="center"><span
        style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US">Women
were not <b style="">&#8220;</b>prohibited<b style="">&#8221;</b> from certain activities<b style="">,</b> it was the circumstances that
prohibited them <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="p40" style="margin-left: 0in; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style=""
                                                                                                           lang="EN-US"><span
        style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>There
are many people who believe that in ancient times and above all in the Bible<b style="">,</b> women were<span style="">&nbsp; </span>scorned and even spurned<b
            style="">.</b> Some have this in their minds because of their misogynistic
atavism<b style="">,</b> but there are some who
mistakenly believe it<b style="">.</b> That did not
occur in the Biblical culture<b style="">,</b> but
that was introduced to that region as of the imposition of the Islamic religion<b style="">.</b> The false religions are
distinguishable for having two extreme and erroneous positions towards women<b style="">:</b><span style="">&nbsp;
</span>some scorn them and others see them as semi-goddesses<b style="">.</b> <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="p40" style="margin-left: 0in; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style=""
                                                                                                           lang="EN-US"><span
        style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>The
fact that women were not more outstanding in ancient cultures was because in
past times<b style="">,</b> </span><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
                                         lang="EN-US">physical
strength was indispensable to excel in society<b style="">.</b> </span><span style="" lang="EN-US"><o:p></o:p></span>
</p>

<p class="p40" style="margin-left: 0in; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style=""
                                                                                                           lang="EN-US"><span
        style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Up
until the 1800&#8217;s what existed was a society which because of the lack of the
technical advances of today<b style="">,</b>
required brutal strength<b style="">.</b> Let&#8217;s use
the example of war<b style="">.</b> The ones who
have always exceeded in society have always been war heroes<b style="">.</b> War was characterized by using heavy mace blows<b
            style="">,</b> swords<b style="">,</b> rocks<b style="">,</b> running after
the ones who escape running from their captors and persecutors<b style="">,</b> fighting body to body with the enemy<b
            style="">.</b> None of these things could be done by
women with the efficiency of men<b style="">.</b>
Therefore<b style="">,</b> </span><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
                                        lang="EN-US">they
could not<b style="">,</b> in general be heroines of
war and consequently they could not be influential characters in society<b style="">.</b> </span><span style=""
                                                                                                       lang="EN-US"><span
        style="">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="p40" style="margin-left: 0in; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style=""
                                                                                                           lang="EN-US"><span
        style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>On the
contrary<b style="">,</b> nowadays<b style="">,</b> they are allowed to enlist in the
Army<b style="">,</b> the Navy and in Air Force<b style="">.</b> Any woman can pilot a combat plane<b style="">,</b> extraordinary physical effort is not
needed for it<b style="">.</b> <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="p40" style="margin-left: 0in; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style=""
                                                                                                           lang="EN-US"><span
        style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>We can
say the same about business<b style="">.</b> A woman
in ancient times could dedicate herself to certain and determined businesses<b style="">,</b> but not as much as men<b
            style="">.</b><span style="">&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>We have the case of the woman mentioned in Proverbs 31<b style="">:</b>10-31<b style="">,</b> and <st1:place
            w:st="on"><st1:country-region w:st="on">Lydia</st1:country-region></st1:place>
in Acts 16<b style="">:</b>14<b style="">,</b> they dedicated themselves to businesses they could carry out<b
            style="">.</b> </span><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
                                        lang="EN-US">They
couldn&#8217;t<b style="">,</b> for example<b style="">,</b> take their merchandise to places that
were distant and dangerous like men did </span><span style="" lang="EN-US">riding their camels<b style="">,</b> because due to their physical weakness<b
        style="">,</b> they would be assaulted<b style="">,</b>
raped<b style="">,</b> enslaved or assassinated<b style="">.</b> <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="p40" style="margin-left: 0in; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style=""
                                                                                                           lang="EN-US"><span
        style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Nowadays<b style="">,</b> any woman can safely travel to the
majority of the big cities in the world and conduct extensive business<b style="">.</b> Even they can conduct many of these businesses
without leaving their offices<b style="">,</b> via
telephone<b style="">,</b> fax<b style="">,</b> computer and the banking services in diverse countries<b style="">.</b> <o:p></o:p></span>
</p>

<p class="p40" style="margin-left: 0in; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style=""
                                                                                                           lang="EN-US"><span
        style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
        style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US">If we talk about work on a farm<b
        style="">,</b>
the same thing happens<b style="">.</b> </span><span style="" lang="EN-US">A woman can plow a field on a
tractor or strip down a field full of weeds or undergrowth<b style="">,</b> sitting on a bulldozer<b style="">.</b>
It was not the same in the 1800&#8217;s when the only thing that could be utilized
was the strong arm of a man and the strength of oxen and horses<b style="">.</b> It wasn&#8217;t easy therefore accumulate
riches in agriculture and livestock<b style="">.</b><span style="">&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="p40" style="margin-left: 0in; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style=""
                                                                                                           lang="EN-US"><span
        style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
        style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US">The issue was not that <b
        style="">&#8220;</b>before<b style="">&#8221;</b> a woman was<span style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>scorned<b
        style="">;</b>
</span><span style="" lang="EN-US">the issue was that
before<b style="">,</b> in Biblical times<b style="">,</b> women could not compete in the brutal
world in which she lived in<b style="">.</b> No one
was going to give an opportunity to a competitor woman<b style="">,</b> because they didn&#8217;t give it to a competitor man either<b
            style="">.</b> That is why women were reserved for a
certain type of work or activity<b style="">,</b><span style="">&nbsp; </span>to which they themselves were restricted by
nature<b style="">.</b> That does not mean that
there weren&#8217;t any exceptions<b style="">,</b> but it
was just that<b style="">,</b> exceptions in which<b style="">,</b> for some reason or circumstance not
frequently<b style="">,</b> a woman stood out<b style="">.</b> <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="p93" style="margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style="" lang="EN-US"><span
        style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>As we see<b style="">,</b>
</span><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US">it was not an issue that it was prohibited for a woman
to be outstanding<b style="">;</b> it was that
circumstances did not allow it<b style="">.</b> <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US"><span style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Among the jobs that women did were the
domestic ones<b>,</b> because in the city and in their homes they were safer
than walking alone in the countryside<b>.</b> However<b>,</b> they worked in
the farms in the company of their relatives or neighbors<b>,</b> or in places
close to the city where they lived<b>,</b> which were frequented by the
neighbors and people they knew<b>.</b> It is such a case in which women
shepherded the family sheep</span><b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US">.</span></b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US"> <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="p2" style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal;"><span style="" lang="EN-US"><span
        style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>In
Exodus 2<b style="">:</b>16 we also see that the
daughters of Jethro<b style="">,</b> Moses&#8217;
father-in-law<b style="">,</b> grazed his father&#8217;s
sheep<b style="">.</b> In this special case<b style="">,</b> these women<b style="">,</b> even though they did not receive serious attacks<b
            style="">,</b> they were displaced by other
shepherds<b style="">.</b> Motivated by this abuse
it was that Moses defended them and got involved in Jethro&#8217;s family<b style="">.</b> Rachel was also a shepherd to<span
            style="">&nbsp; </span>the sheep of Laban<b style="">,</b> her father<b style="">.</b><o:p></o:p></span></p>

