        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US"> and I say to her</span><b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
        lang="EN-US">,</span></b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US"> Give me</span><b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
        lang="EN-US">,</span></b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US"> I pray
thee</span><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
                    lang="EN-US">,</span></b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US"> a little
water of thy pitcher to drink</span><b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
        lang="EN-US">.&#8221;</span></b><span style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US"><span style="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>(Genesis 24</span><b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US">:</span></b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US">43)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="p93" style="margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style="" lang="EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span>
</p>

<p class="p93" style="margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style="" lang="EN-US"><span
        style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>There were also other activities that were
particular to men<b style="">,</b> that women did as
is seen in the case of the construction of the walls of <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:city
            w:st="on">Jerusalem</st1:city></st1:place> by Nehemiah<b style="">.</b> <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span>
</p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0.2in 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"
                                                                                    lang="EN-US"><span style=""> </span></span><b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
        lang="EN-US">&#8220;</span></b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US">And next unto him repaired Shallum the son of Halohesh</span><b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
        lang="EN-US">,</span></b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US"> the
ruler of the half part of Jerusalem</span><b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
        lang="EN-US">,</span></b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
        lang="EN-US"> he </span><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US">and
his daughters</span><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
                             lang="EN-US">.&#8221;</span></b><span style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US"><span style="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>(Nehemiah
3</span><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US">:</span></b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US">12)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span>
</p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US"><span style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>In this case<b>,</b> not just a woman but a
whole family of them were working in the restoration of the walls of the city
of <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:city w:st="on">Jerusalem</st1:city></st1:place><b>.</b>
Undoubtedly this means one of two things<b>,</b> either these women practiced
architecture or worked in masonry<b>.</b><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US"><span style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>In general<b>,</b> when it came to the activities
of women<b>,</b> there were no prohibitive rules<b>,</b> it was they themselves<b>,</b>
who knew that physically they could not compete<b>,</b> and moved away<b>.</b>
However<b>,</b> those women who considered themselves capable of doing
something<b>,</b> did so without anyone bothering them<b>.</b> <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US"><span style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US">As
for social activities<b>,</b> </span><span style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US">it is perceived that they participated as much as the
men as we see in the following passage from Job<b>.</b> <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span>
</p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0.2in 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"
                                                                                    lang="EN-US"><span style=""> </span></span><b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
        lang="EN-US">&#8220;</span></b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US">And his sons went and feasted in their houses</span><b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
        lang="EN-US">,</span></b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US"> every
one his day</span><b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
        lang="EN-US">;</span></b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold Italic&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US"> and
sent and called for their three sisters to eat and to drink with them</span><b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
        lang="EN-US">.&#8221;</span></b><span style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US"><span style="">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>(Job
1</span><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;" lang="EN-US">:</span></b><span
        style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US">4)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0.2in 0.0001pt; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"
                                                                                    lang="EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span>
</p>

<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US"><span style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><b>In general,</b> it could be said that
women had liberty<b>,</b> but circumstances<b>,</b> competition and the nature
of their sex limited them greatly<b>.</b> Because<span style="">&nbsp; </span>of the fact of being women and become
pregnant and have to care for newborns<b>,</b> limited them in the use of their
time and in the amount of strength they could dedicate to excel in politically<b>,</b>
socially and economically<b>.</b> This does not mean that none of them did<b>,</b>
what it means is that there were always more impediments for women than for men<b>.</b>
It is good to analyze these things because this allows us to understand the
customs and upon doing so<b>,</b> it helps us to interpret Scripture correctly<b>.</b>
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

